review.body:
## Code Review

This pull request introduces a significant and well-executed refactoring of the core logic, aligning with SOLID principles and clean code practices. The decomposition of the `StressTestEngine` into smaller, single-responsibility components is a major improvement for maintainability and testability. The introduction of interfaces for dependency injection is also a great step forward. I have identified a couple of areas for improvement: one regarding duplicated code in the new interfaces file, and another suggesting a cleaner way to handle a circular dependency that was noted as a 'hack' in the code. Overall, these are excellent changes that greatly improve the project's architecture.

issue.body:
### Bambu Studio Version

2.0.3.54

### Where is the application from?

Bambu Lab Official website

### OS version

MacOS

### Additional system information

N/A

### Printer

H2D

### How to reproduce

1. Go to Support settings in any profile.
2. Search for "interface layers" --> see that bottom interface layers appears (is an option in Orca and elsewhere) in search: ![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c24de21d-4e66-4445-aa6b-e43bc850ffae)
3. Go look at the ACTUAL list of options you can change... you cannot find Bottom Interface layers anywhere: ![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0ad150e3-3467-42de-83d9-1be93f97864f)


### Actual results

Can't find bottom interface layers setting, but I cannot because it's hidden.

### Expected results

Bottom interface layers setting should be exposed in UX.

**I want to change the bottom interface layers setting, but I cannot because it's hidden.**

### Project file & Debug log uploads

N/A.

### Checklist of files to include

issue.title: CheatMaster (Cheatsheet Template Generator) (SSoC '25)
issue.body:
This PR introduces a simple and customizable Cheatsheet Template Generator for HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
It comes pre-filled with essential syntax and commands, while also allowing users to add, remove, or edit their snippets for a fully personalized cheatsheet.

Features:

- Pre-filled entries for HTML, CSS, and JavaScript
- Custom snippet creation ‚Äî add your own topics, descriptions, and code blocks
- Remove entries instantly when no longer needed
- Copy to clipboard with one click
- Print support for quick offline reference
- Light/Dark theme toggle for comfortable reading
- Local storage support ‚Äî saves your entries automatically between sessions
- Responsive design for mobile and desktop
-Fixed footer for consistent branding and navigation

Ideal for:

1. Web development learners
2. Students preparing for exams or interviews
3. Developers needing quick syntax access
